news.title: Tamil Nadu: Suggestions for draft rehabilitation policy for slum dwellers can be submitted till Nov 3
news.para: The draft policy states that the policy is applicable only for encroacher/non-titleholders of the land, where displacement is proposed for involuntary resettlement.

news.title: Mysuru development body hopes to get nod for group housing project in Nov
news.para: If things go according to plans, Muda will construct high-rise structures at three places - two in west Mysuru and one in east Mysuru. The urban development body has reserved Rs 100 crores for its ambitious project. The total cost of the project is estimated at Rs 372 crores.

news.title: Lodha Luxury pays tribute to healthcare & wellness leaders at Raj Bhavan
news.para: On the occasion of World Mental Health Day, celebrated on 10th October, Lodha Luxury, a leading real estate player and creator of luxury residences, paid its tribute to eminent healthcare and wellness leaders and their families.

news.title: Now, sub-registrars can grant mutation during property registration in Goa
news.para: The revenue department has issued a notification to grant powers of the mamlatdar to the sub-registrar and registration officers in the state so that mutation records can be updated simultaneously while property transactions are registered or when there is a change in the ownership of a particular plot of land.

news.title: China Evergrande Group resumes work on more than 10 property projects
news.para: Evergrande, deep in crisis with more than $300 billion in liabilities, has not disclosed how many of its 1,300 real estate projects across China it has had to halt work on.

news.title: Development work has started on Seawoods plot in Navi Mumbai: Environmentalists
news.para: ​Last week, TOI had reported that a MahaRera certificate for the Seawoods plot was recently acquired, although the legal dispute is ongoing in the SC. Cidco had given building permissions to the developer in 2018. Based on these permissions, MahaRera registered the project.

news.title: Livspace to invest Rs 187.5 crore in JV with ASG to expand in Saudi Arabia
news.para: According to  Livspace co-founder Ramakant Sharma, the company’s current revenue run-rate is around $175-180 million, which is expected to grow to $300-350 million within the next two years.

news.title: Wipro leases 3.5 lakh sq ft at Mindspace Business Park in Navi Mumbai
news.para: The IT Special Economic Zone (SEZ), Mindspace Airoli East is a property owned and operated by K Raheja Corp and Blackstone Group-backed listed Mindspace Business Parks Real Estate Investment Trust (REIT).

news.title: Delhi court grants bail to directors of Parsvnath Developers in cheating case
news.para: Pradeep Kumar Jain, Rajeev Jain and Sanjeev Kumar Jain were granted bail after they appeared before the court in pursuance to summons issued against them earlier in the case of cheating and criminal breach of trust.

news.title: Gujarat government approves Ahmedabad civic body's new parking policy
news.para: The Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation’s new parking policy has been cleared by the state government and will be implemented soon in a phased manner.

news.title: Jharkhand: Urban amenities to be brought on digital monitoring platform
news.para: The centralised portal will be a part of the proposed National Urban Digital Mission and will be implemented in the state through state urban development department.

news.title: Delhi court reserves order on Avantha Group's bail plea till October 30
news.para: The ED was probing an alleged transaction between Thapar's company Avantha Realty and YES Bank co-founder Rana Kapoor and his wife, who are already being investigated under the Prevention of Money Laundering Act (PMLA) by the agency.

news.title: Chennai: Redevelopment of Egmore railway station delayed
news.para: Since it took almost seven years after the corporation was formed to include Egmore on the list of stations to be developed, shutting down of the corporation will delay it further

news.title: Illegal construction in Corbett Tiger Reserve example of administration failure: NTCA
news.para: NTCA has found that in order to allow illegal construction of roads and building in Corbett Tiger Reserve, Forest Officer has forged the Government records.

news.title: Maharashtra government proposes change in policy to give TDR demand a boost
news.para: The rights of finalising the priority between the TDR and premium FSI has been given to the municipal commissioner’s office. The directives would be implemented after the government seeks objections and suggestions from the public for its clearance.
